	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=131896><span id= >Vintaro</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Just wanted to throw my 2 cents in here.<br><br>There is some pretty accurate information posted on this subject. And of course there are still some questions. Here are some answers and explanations of things that were not covered.<br><br>Here is a tactic I use when pulling to split mobs. Naturally you aggro the and run a good distance from their spawn location before feigning.( make sure you can stil see where you pulled the from) You then wait for all but 1 or 2 to return to their spawn location before standing up. If all goes well only those should retain aggro. To make this easier I cast darkness on teh mob that I want to pull first and run a bit farther then normal from the spawn location. The mob then will take longer to get back to the others and wam , he is all yours. Mob Lvl may cause you some grief when doing this at lower lvls. I am 60 so it does not matter.<br><br>Here is a tactic I use when feigning against casters.(this only works if you have a wall of some type near you.) Never try to feign if a mob starts to cast a spell. 15 seconds is forever to try to feign again. If there are walls enar you run so that the mob cannot see you. after he casts the first spell he should run to get Line of sight on you before he casts again. This is the perfect time to cast FD. If multiple casters run far around walls and you will have plenty of time to fd. If you have casters adn melee's follow the same preocedure and hope you are not interupted before the&nbsp;&nbsp;casters get to you again.<br><br>Feign Death can also be used to transfer aggro from you to another tank. This is sometimes a good tactic depending on the situation. Alot of times I can out aggro the warriors in my group and I want them to have aggro so I can be free to pull some more mobs.<br><br>Here is how you reduce the chance of FD interupts. Actually it works for any spell caster. Place a wall directly behind you. Interupts for the most part are caused by a mob pushing you with either spells or melee damage. Now remeber this is not 100% but will help you out alot more then you may think. Also turn off your attack before you try to fd. It really does make a difference.<br><br>SK, Necro FD = 15 second recast.<br>Monk FD = 10 second reuse.<br>SK Deathpeace = 3 second recast(maybe 4)<br><br>We got hooked up. When you hit 60 yo will do alot more pulling then you ever imagined and will learn tons of tricks to prevent aggro and Single pull Mobs. here are a few.<br><br>I prefer to use Shadow Vortex to pull with. Its fast, low mana, and creates alot of aggro. This allows me to pull past other groups and prevent the mobs from hitting the casters that are sitting when I do get to camp.<br><br>To single pull multiple mobs try to aggro the highest level mobs only. This should keep the lower lvl mobs still standing there. <br><br>If you are trying to get back to camp and the path is now blocked by caster mobs, wait until they cast a buff on themselves. As soon as they do you can run right past them without aggro. If you are too close when they finish casting they will aggro.<br><br>If you just dont have enough hitpoints to get that mob back to camp FD. Face the direction the mob came from. Wait till he is pretty far away and get up and run to camp. The mob should still have aggro and you will still be alive. Repeat if necessary. I use this tactic when I am pulling Hall of testing in Temple of Veeshan. Some of the mobs are just too fast in running speed and melee speed.<br><br>Well that is all I can think of at the moment. Feigning is an art and with time you will come to realize that FD and Death Peace are the best spells you will ever scribe.<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Dec 30 08:54:41 2001</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Vintaro Tel'Quessir<br>60 GraveLord<br>Valde Amicitia<br>Rodcet Nife<br><br></td></td></tr>
